ActFamily Orders and Agreements Enforcement Assistance Act
SubjectRegulations Amending Certain Regulations Made Under the Family Orders and Agreements Enforcement Assistance Act
PrecisRegulations amending CERTAIN REGULATIONS MADE UNDER THE FAMILY ORDERS AND AGREEMENTS ENFORCEMENT ASSISTANCE ACT in order to promote and protect gender equality, diversity and inclusion by (1) requiring that applicants indicate the gender of support debtors or persons to be located rather than their sex, and the "Surname at birth of each parent" of the person; and (2) adding two additional options to the application forms, such as "another gender" and "information not available".
